00:50:43.977 --> 00:50:45.560 align:middle line:84%
They would have
outside jobs-- but yet

00:50:45.560 --> 00:50:49.311 align:middle line:84%
still require themselves
to do something

00:50:49.311 --> 00:50:51.560 align:middle line:84%
that contributes to the
greater role of the community.

00:50:51.560 --> 00:50:53.780 align:middle line:84%
>>HUBBARD: And many of them
don't have outside jobs.

00:50:53.780 --> 00:50:56.420 align:middle line:84%
They're really working to
make that community work.

00:50:56.420 --> 00:50:57.710 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, my goodness.

00:50:57.710 --> 00:50:59.130 align:middle line:90%
Fantastic idea.

00:50:59.130 --> 00:51:00.950 align:middle line:84%
I know that there
are so many things

00:51:00.950 --> 00:51:02.400 align:middle line:90%
that we can do in our future.

00:51:02.400 --> 00:51:05.190 align:middle line:84%
That's just I would see
a way of the future.

00:51:05.190 --> 00:51:07.749 align:middle line:84%
There are a lot
of new structures

00:51:07.749 --> 00:51:10.290 align:middle line:84%
that are being built like that,
not just apartment buildings.

00:51:10.290 --> 00:51:11.630 align:middle line:90%
But there are communities.

00:51:11.630 --> 00:51:13.520 align:middle line:84%
And people that live
in these new buildings

00:51:13.520 --> 00:51:16.650 align:middle line:84%
all commune together to
work within the community

00:51:16.650 --> 00:51:17.450 align:middle line:90%
of the building.

00:51:17.450 --> 00:51:20.690 align:middle line:84%
So there's ways that
entire cities are being

00:51:20.690 --> 00:51:22.970 align:middle line:90%
built around this structure.

00:51:22.970 --> 00:51:24.830 align:middle line:84%
>>HUBBARD: I think the
most important thing

00:51:24.830 --> 00:51:30.500 align:middle line:84%
we can do right now is connect
innovations already working

00:51:30.500 --> 00:51:38.570 align:middle line:84%
in an office for the future in
a public media new news show.

00:51:38.570 --> 00:51:42.170 align:middle line:90%
I want to do a new news show.

00:51:42.170 --> 00:51:44.980 align:middle line:84%
First I was going to tell
what's his name on CNN,

00:51:44.980 --> 00:51:45.780 align:middle line:90%
Anderson Cooper.

00:51:45.780 --> 00:51:49.100 align:middle line:84%
Can you give me 10 minutes
for the new news, please?

00:51:49.100 --> 00:51:52.370 align:middle line:84%
But I thought, why would
I get 10 minutes on CNN?

00:51:52.370 --> 00:51:53.820 align:middle line:90%
Why not have a new news show?

00:51:53.820 --> 00:51:54.620 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:51:54.620 --> 00:51:56.690 align:middle line:84%
I've had the same
exact vision, Barbara,

00:51:56.690 --> 00:51:58.520 align:middle line:90%
of a new show with solutions.

00:51:58.520 --> 00:52:00.900 align:middle line:84%
>>HUBBARD: And the new
news, and that's the news.

00:52:00.900 --> 00:52:06.350 align:middle line:84%
Actually, what doesn't
work is called the news.

00:52:06.350 --> 00:52:07.710 align:middle line:90%
That's wrong.

00:52:07.710 --> 00:52:08.510 align:middle line:90%
That's wrong.

00:52:08.510 --> 00:52:09.499 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I agree 100%.

00:52:09.499 --> 00:52:10.790 align:middle line:90%
And I think it's irresponsible.

00:52:10.790 --> 00:52:11.270 align:middle line:90%
>>HUBBARD: It's not accurate.

00:52:11.270 --> 00:52:13.010 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I think it's
downright irresponsible.

00:52:13.010 --> 00:52:13.850 align:middle line:90%
>>HUBBARD: It's not accurate.

00:52:13.850 --> 00:52:14.970 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Not any longer.

00:52:14.970 --> 00:52:16.790 align:middle line:84%
I think we need to
have, here's the facts,

00:52:16.790 --> 00:52:19.540 align:middle line:90%
but here's 10 solutions.

00:52:19.540 --> 00:52:21.960 align:middle line:84%
>>HUBBARD: See, even the
word "solutions" you might--

00:52:21.960 --> 00:52:25.070 align:middle line:90%
the new news is what's new.

00:52:25.070 --> 00:52:27.410 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't call it
like, I'm a solution.

00:52:27.410 --> 00:52:28.930 align:middle line:90%
Do you what I'm saying?

00:52:28.930 --> 00:52:32.420 align:middle line:84%
I'm an impulsive creation that's
doing this and this and this.

00:52:32.420 --> 00:52:35.240 align:middle line:84%
The word "solution" is a
little bit too limited.

00:52:35.240 --> 00:52:36.380 align:middle line:90%
Here's a problem.

00:52:36.380 --> 00:52:37.430 align:middle line:90%
Here's a solution.

00:52:37.430 --> 00:52:38.720 align:middle line:90%
Yes, that's good.

00:52:38.720 --> 00:52:42.160 align:middle line:84%
But we're talking about
building a culture of love,

00:52:42.160 --> 00:52:44.150 align:middle line:90%
of creativity, of wholeness.

00:52:44.150 --> 00:52:46.430 align:middle line:84%
That's not a solution
to a problem.

00:52:46.430 --> 00:52:48.690 align:middle line:84%
That's the evolution
of the species.

00:52:48.690 --> 00:52:51.420 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So it would be
news into the future.

00:52:51.420 --> 00:52:55.130 align:middle line:84%
>>HUBBARD: Yes, and wherever
innovations are working.

00:52:55.130 --> 00:52:58.055 align:middle line:84%
And I would take what Ilya
Prigogine-- won the Nobel Prize

00:52:58.055 --> 00:53:01.040 align:middle line:84%
for dissipative structures--
how did nature get

00:53:01.040 --> 00:53:03.590 align:middle line:90%
from disorder to higher order?

00:53:03.590 --> 00:53:06.020 align:middle line:10%
By connecting what's
innovative and creative

00:53:06.020 --> 00:53:09.210 align:middle line:10%
when the system
is dysfunctional.

00:53:09.210 --> 00:53:11.210 align:middle line:90%
We have a dysfunctional system.

00:53:11.210 --> 00:53:13.940 align:middle line:84%
We have innovations
that are rising.

00:53:13.940 --> 00:53:17.510 align:middle line:10%
So let's connect--
not only just connect,

00:53:17.510 --> 00:53:20.780 align:middle line:10%
but synergize, which
is, I need this.

00:53:20.780 --> 00:53:22.850 align:middle line:90%
Can you help me create that?

00:53:22.850 --> 00:53:25.580 align:middle line:84%
I will help you create
what you need to do--

00:53:25.580 --> 00:53:29.460 align:middle line:84%
vocational arousal
and joining genius.

00:53:29.460 --> 00:53:31.150 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes, yes, yes.

00:53:31.150 --> 00:53:37.730 align:middle line:84%
I end every show is asking
you, what is your biggest why?

00:53:37.730 --> 00:53:40.970 align:middle line:84%
>>HUBBARD: I thought about that
when you mentioned it to me.

00:53:40.970 --> 00:53:45.950 align:middle line:84%
My biggest why is
abnormal cruelty.

00:53:45.950 --> 00:53:53.410 align:middle line:84%
It's completely impossible for
me to accept abnormal cruelty,

00:53:53.410 --> 00:53:56.620 align:middle line:84%
whether it be to an animal,
or to one another, torture.

00:53:56.620 --> 00:53:58.780 align:middle line:90%
I mean, I cannot imagine it.

00:53:58.780 --> 00:54:03.000 align:middle line:84%
So then the biggest why
is, what happened there

00:54:03.000 --> 00:54:06.340 align:middle line:90%
that so many of us can be cruel?

00:54:06.340 --> 00:54:09.910 align:middle line:84%
And I've asked, is it
a nervous system defect

00:54:09.910 --> 00:54:14.440 align:middle line:84%
where empathy is not as natural
to some people as it could be?

00:54:14.440 --> 00:54:18.670 align:middle line:84%
Because if you are empathetic,
you could not do that.

00:54:18.670 --> 00:54:21.180 align:middle line:84%
You could not torture another
person if you were empathetic.

00:54:21.180 --> 00:54:22.420 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes, you are correct.

00:54:22.420 --> 00:54:24.680 align:middle line:84%
And this is your
biggest motivator.

00:54:24.680 --> 00:54:27.700 align:middle line:10%
>>HUBBARD: Yes, the
mass empathy and love.

00:54:27.700 --> 00:54:31.930 align:middle line:10%
And so by connecting more of us
who are empathetic and loving,

00:54:31.930 --> 00:54:35.190 align:middle line:10%
we create a new field
of consciousness.

00:54:35.190 --> 00:54:38.680 align:middle line:84%
And you know, that word "field"
is really accurate here.

00:54:38.680 --> 00:54:41.450 align:middle line:84%
It's not just any one
project or one solution.

00:54:41.450 --> 00:54:46.570 align:middle line:84%
It's an attitudinal field
that reinforces love and makes

00:54:46.570 --> 00:54:48.384 align:middle line:90%
cruelty almost impossible.

00:54:48.384 --> 00:54:49.800 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's a
beautiful reason.

00:54:49.800 --> 00:54:51.070 align:middle line:90%
And I join you in that.

00:54:51.070 --> 00:54:51.945 align:middle line:90%
>>HUBBARD: Thank you.

00:54:51.945 --> 00:54:53.260 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And thank you for that.

00:54:53.260 --> 00:54:57.430 align:middle line:84%
And thank you for creating this
incredible energy and resource

00:54:57.430 --> 00:55:00.576 align:middle line:84%
